                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">15 incomplete lines of writing on the front, back blank</note>
                     <note type="general">incomplete on all sides, 3 fragments glued together</note>
                     <note type="general">the text is difficult to decipher not because the pottery is dark (as in ed.pr.) but because it is faded and discolored in parts</note>
                     <note type="general">the hand, which is somewhat irregular with letters of varying size, is very similar and perhaps identical to the hand of Mon.Epiph. 598 etc</note>
